.TH "devm_usb_get_phy" 9 "devm_usb_get_phy" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_usb_get_phy \- find the USB PHY
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct usb_phy *" devm_usb_get_phy
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "enum usb_phy_type type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device that requests this phy
.IP "type" 12
the type of the phy the controller requires
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Gets the phy using \fBusb_get_phy\fP, and associates a device with it using
devres. On driver detach, release function is invoked on the devres data,
then, devres data is freed.

For use by USB host and peripheral drivers.
